* Good things to know
  1. '=M=' refers to the "meta" key, aka the "alt" key on most keyboards today
  2. '=C=' refers to the "control" key
  3. '=M-x=' is by default bound to =(execute-extended-command)= and is going to be one of the keybinds you most often use
  4. '=C-g=' runs =(keyboard-quit)= It is /the/ most useful keybind in Emacs
  5. I just wanted to mention those.... there's a few other really useful ones but I'm sure you already know them
     - If you don't, I highly recommend the *[[https://www.emacswiki.org][Emacs Wiki]]*

